<h2 align="center">About the work</h2><div><div>The 'Heritage Platform' is a collaborative space for addressing heritage-related challenges and sharing successful practices. It brings together civil society organizations (CSOs) focused on cultural heritage and environmental protection to promote the safeguarding of both tangible and intangible cultural heritage while sharing best practices for the well-being of all.</div><div><br></div><div>Launched in February 2023 with support from the EU, the Platform plays an active role in advocacy efforts aimed at preserving the historical areas of Tbilisi and the cultural heritage monuments in Kutaisi and Dusheti.</div><div><br></div><div>Currently, the Platform unites 13 organizations from across Georgia and invites new members, particularly CSOs or initiative groups whose voices may not yet be heard and who require support in heritage protection.</div><div><br></div><div>To learn more about the Platformâ€™s work, explore our detailed activities in social <a href="https://bit.ly/3qjhXzH">media</a></div></div>